The implementation looks correct to me. I've covered all the requirements from the spec:

1. Boot leaves inlet closed and heater off ✓
2. Stay in safe state until both sensors valid ✓
3. Level < 60 → INLET OPEN, HEATER OFF (FILLING) ✓
4. Level > 75 → INLET CLOSED ✓
5. Level < 55 → HEATER OFF (at any time) ✓
6. 60 <= level <= 75 AND temp < 45 → INLET CLOSED, HEATER ON (HEATING) ✓
7. 45 <= temp < 47 → INLET CLOSED, hold previous heater state (HOLDING) ✓
8. 47 <= temp <= 48 AND rising → HEATER OFF early (HOLDING) ✓
9. 47 <= temp <= 48 AND not rising → hold previous heater state (HOLDING) ✓
10. Temp > 48 → INLET CLOSED, HEATER OFF (SAFE_IDLE) ✓
11. Timeout/malformed input → SAFE_IDLE ✓

My tests all pass and cover the main scenarios from the spec. The implementation follows the control policy as specified.

